    "scoring_notes": "Respondents rate each statement on a 5-point scale (1 = Very Inaccurate, 2 = Moderately Inaccurate, 3 = Neither Inaccurate nor Accurate, 4 = Moderately Accurate, 5 = Very Accurate) under the instruction to describe themselves as they generally are now, honestly, relative to others of the same sex and roughly the same age. Items keyed \"+\" are scored 1->5; items keyed \"-\" are reverse-scored (5->1). Each of the 30 facet scores is the sum (or mean) of its 4 items (raw sum range 4-20); each of the 5 domain scores (N, E, O, A, C) is the mean/sum of its 6 constituent facets. \"num\" is the item's position in the 120-item administration order (the \"IPIP-120 item no.\" column in Johnson, 2014, Table 1); the parent IPIP-NEO-300 uses different item numbers, not included here.",
    "cautions": "These are the ORIGINAL, terse IPIP item stems (short first-person predicate phrases such as \"Worry about things.\") captured verbatim for a stage-1 corpus intended to be rewritten into plain language. Item text was taken verbatim from the official IPIP repository page (ipip.ori.org/30FacetNEO-PI-RItems.htm); the administration item numbers (1-120), factor, facet, and +/- keying were independently cross-checked against Johnson (2014) Table 1 (the Penn State PDF) — every keying sign matched across both sources, and all 30 facets have exactly 4 items. One minor wording variant exists: item 58 (O6 Liberalism) reads \"Believe that there is no absolute right and wrong\" on ipip.ori.org (used here) but is typeset as \"right or wrong\" in Johnson (2014) Table 1; the IPIP repository wording is used. Keying is intentionally imbalanced (65 positively-keyed, 55 negatively-keyed) because Johnson selected items purely by item-total correlation, so several facets are all-one-direction (e.g., E5, E6, O1, C1 are entirely +; A2, A4, A5, C6 are entirely -). Apostrophes were normalized to straight ASCII to match the HTML source. Items are listed as bare stems without a leading pronoun; some live administrations of Johnson's IPIP-NEO prepend an \"I\" to each statement. | 번역본: 문항 순서·채점방향(keyed)·factor/facet은 원본과 동일. text_en에 원문 병기.",
